                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On June 19, 1948, the Department of State cabled revised texts of its master
                    Economic Cooperation Agreement to its missions in <gloss target="#t_CEEC1"
                        >CEEC</gloss> countries for transmission to the respective governments. The
                    new text was expected to meet the objections that had been made to the previous
                    text. In a circular telegram of June 14, the Department had advised its
                    representatives as to appropriate procedures for preparing signature copies
                    which were to be signed in the foreign capitals concerned.</p>
            </div>
